# Plain English

Paste any document. Get back a version you can actually understand.

Terms of service, lease agreements, insurance policies, employment contracts, medical consent forms, government notices, privacy policies, academic papers, code — it reads the document, flags the dangerous clauses, replaces the jargon, and tells you what you agreed to.

No AI. No internet. Your text never leaves the page.

-----

## What it does

**For legal and policy documents:**

- Detects document type automatically (or you pick manually)
- Flags red-flag clauses: mandatory arbitration, class action waivers, auto-renewal traps, data selling, liability caps, broad license grants, and more
- Replaces legal jargon with plain English inline — hover to see the original term
- Scores reading complexity (Flesch-Kincaid)
- Gives a plain verdict and risk level

**For code:**

- Explains HTML tags, CSS properties, JavaScript patterns, and Python patterns in plain language
- Detects the language automatically

**For scientific text:**

- Decodes binomial species names, chemical formulas, and Latin/Greek medical terminology

-----

## Stack

Vanilla HTML, CSS, JavaScript. No build step. No dependencies.

-----

## Run locally

```bash
npx serve .
# open http://localhost:3000
```

Or just open `index.html` directly — works in most browsers. If you see a blank page, use `npx serve` instead (Chrome’s local file restrictions).

Works fully offline. Google Fonts are the only external request.

-----

## Deploy

Drop the folder on any static host. Nothing to configure.

-----

## Project structure

```
index.html
css/
  base.css            — resets, variables
  layout.css          — page structure
  components.css      — all component styles
  responsive.css      — mobile breakpoints
js/
  data/
    jargon.js         — 300+ term replacement dictionary
    redFlags.js       — dangerous clause patterns
    docTypes.js       — document type detection rules
  engines/
    general.js        — complexity scoring, flag detection, jargon replacement
    code.js           — HTML/CSS/JS/Python explainer
    science.js        — species names, chemical formulas, medical terms
  app.js              — routing, UI, session history, draft persistence
  sampleContent.js    — sample documents for each category
test-data/            — 12 regression test files across all document types
```

-----

## Regression tests

12 test files covering every supported document type. Pass rate: 12/12.

To run them:

```bash
node run-regression-tests.js
```

